# ViewModel, Repository, and View

## Layer boundaries

| Layer | Responsibility | Must not |
|-------|----------------|----------|
| **View (Composable)** | Render `UIState`, forward `UIEvent`, observe one-shot navigation | Call repositories, `HttpClient`, or DataStore; own business rules |
| **ViewModel** | Orchestrate use cases, map data → state, emit `UIDirections`, handle errors/loading | Import Compose; leak `Context`/platform types in `commonMain` |
| **Repository** | One bounded data concern (API, preferences, cache); stable API for the VM | Navigate or hold UI-specific types; mix unrelated domains in one class |

## Repository

- Name with domain + `Repository` (e.g. `PreferencesRepository`, `OrdersRepository`).
- Expose **suspend** functions for single requests and **Flow** for observable streams (already the pattern in `PreferencesRepository`).
- Parse/map network or storage models here; ViewModels receive types that are convenient for UI or a thin domain model.
- Register with `@Single` unless a new instance per injection is required (`@Factory`).
- Keep `commonMain` repositories free of Android-only APIs; use `expect`/`actual` when platform bits are needed.

## ViewModel (`BaseViewModel`)

- Constructor-inject only repositories/use-case-style types — not `NavController`.
- Override `defaultUIState()` with the full initial state; update with `_state.value = _state.value.copy(...)`.
- Handle async work in **`viewModelScope.launch`** (or `launch` on the VM’s scope from `BaseViewModel`), switch context inside when calling blocking or IO-bound repo methods (`withContext(Dispatchers.IO) { ... }` if the repo is not already main-safe).
- On success/failure, update state (e.g. loading flag, error message, data). Use **`navigate(...)`** only for navigation intents, not for “business success” that belongs in state unless the product explicitly navigates on completion.
- Override **`onEvent`**: call `super.onEvent(event)`, then exhaustive `when` on sealed `UIEvent`s.

## View

- Follow the screen split in **Compose UI conventions**: outer composable collects `state` with **`collectAsStateWithLifecycle()`**, passes **`onEvent = viewModel::onEvent`** into stateless content.
- **`LaunchedEffect`** at the screen edge: collect `viewModel.directions` and map to `NavController` / platform navigation — keep navigation wiring out of child composables when possible.
- Do not read `viewModel.state.value` directly in composition without collection; prefer reactive collection so recompositions stay correct.

## Feature layout (suggested)

Colocate `FeatureScreen.kt`, `FeatureViewModel.kt`, and optional `FeatureRepository.kt` under the same feature package (e.g. `ui/feature/`) as the app grows; shared repositories stay under `datastore/`, `network/`, etc.
